    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1874-03-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1874-03-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="253" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d253">
                <head>No. 552.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Fish</persName> to Admiral <persName type="to">Polo de
                                    Bernabé</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1874-03-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">March</hi> 28,
                                1874</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to transmit herewith for
                            your consideration a copy of the report<note n="*" xml:id="d253fn1">See
                                Nos. 550, 551.</note> of a naval court of inquiry convened under the
                            direction of the President, by an order of the Secretary of the Navy,
                            promulgated on the 3d of January last, to inquire into the causes of the
                            foundering of the steamer Virginius, then recently delivered to the
                            United States by order of the government of Spain.</p>
                <p>The report contains all the evidence, documentary and oral, submitted to
                            the court of inquiry in relation to the subject of the inquiry on that
                            occasion.</p>
                <p>Accept, sir, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>HAMILTON FISH.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
